    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl> Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>290</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2010"/>, p. <citedRange>98</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>60.1828</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>106400</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65125"><name nymRef="#Νίκανδρος">Νίκανδρος</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65073"><name nymRef="#Μυρσίλος" type="patronymic">Μυρσίλω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Nikandros fils de Myrsilos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Nikandros son of Myrsilos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Nikandros son of Myrsilos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Unfortunately the stone could not be photographed and no squeeze was made. We can only offer a drawing.</p>
	<p>The father's name is a variant of <foreign xml:lang="grc">Μύρτιλος</foreign>, which is more common in the region both in reference to the plant which 
	    also produced the epithet of Apollo Myrtoos and with the name of a mythical hero (see <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2010"/>, p. <citedRange>98</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
